<br>
The icy caverns of Permafrost assaulted my senses.  The strong breeze felt strangely like fresh air, but I knew this must be the place.  The crowding of the other adventurers who had gathered for this momentous occasion made that quite clear.<br>
<br>
Karmel auctions &quot;WTS lamentation - serious tells only&quot;<br>
<br>
Strange I thought, to be arranging for equipment so late in the hunt of such a mighty beast<br>
<br>
Smithy auctions &quot;WTS BABS, BAL, FBR, FBSS - WTB Good warrior armor&quot;<br>
Sowsalot auctions &quot;TP to any location for 20pp a head&quot;<br>
<br>
Such poor planning and cowardism from my group.  Vox's mighty presence was already forcing the warriors to call into question their defenses and the druids to consider early evacuation.  I fortified my resolve to assault the dragon.<br>
<br>
Helmgest auctions &quot;WTS small bronze armor - 2pp per AC&quot;<br>
Gellan auctions &quot;That is overpriced - stop trying to rip everyone off&quot;<br>
Helmgest auctions &quot;Don't like it, don't buy it&quot;<br>
<br>
The petty infighting was the last straw.  I knew this effort was doomed to fail.  With no thought of the consequences, I turned to flee - willing to brave ice giants and goblins alike versus the sure death of this ill-fated assault.  I stumbled into a body - an elite warrior of the goblin king no doubt - and drew my weapon to slash at him.<br>
<br>
Gellan says &quot;Who is that guy attacking the shady swashbuckler with the milk bottle?&quot;<br>
Helmgest says &quot;No idea&quot; <br>
<br>
NEXT EPISODE:  Viraan buys a moonstone from shady<br>
<br>
Viraan says &quot;Take this platinum in payment&quot;<br>
Shady says &quot;Um... that's a chunk of meat&quot;<br>
<br>
Renien Fyrefeat<br>
Storyteller of 30 Seasons<br>
